Introduction

SKYE (Korean: 스카이; Japanese: スカイ; formerly IN2IT) is a six-member boy group formed through the survival show BOYS24. Originally as eight, they debuted on October 26, 2017 with the mini album Carpe Diem.On February 10, 2020, the group parted ways with MMO Entertainment after contract termination.

On March 16, 2023, IN2IT announced they've renamed their group name to SKYE

On August 5, 2023 they announced their first sub unit CoA consisting of Yeontae and Jiahn, they will begin their promotions in Japan starting in September.
